com.kuka.geometry

Class PhysicalObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.kuka.geometry.SpatialObject
      • com.kuka.geometry.PhysicalObject
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ICapabilityContainer, IMovable, IMovableObject
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Tool

    public class PhysicalObject
extends SpatialObject
implements IMovableObject
    Represents a real physical object that may be part of a scene graph.

    Motions can be requested for physical objects (see IMovableObject). They can optionally possess load data getLoadData() which allows to set mass, center of mass and inertia of the physical object.

    Changes of structure and properties can be monitored by registering for events on SpatialObject.getEventProvider(). For further information about available events see TreeEvent and its subclasses.

    See Also:
    PhysicalObjectUtils

      • removeFrame

        public void removeFrame(ObjectFrame frame)
        Removes the specified object frame from the object and disconnects it from its parent frame.

        The frame tree below the disconnected frame stays intact. This operation is not allowed if another spatial object has a connection to the frame to remove (or to any of its descendants), since this would sever the connection to the child object.

        Overrides:
        removeFrame in class SpatialObject
        Parameters:
        frame - the frame to be removed.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - in any of the following cases:
        • the given frame is null
        • the given frame is the root frame of the object
        • the given frame does not belong to this object
        • the given frame is a default frame (see SpatialObject.getDefaultAttachmentFrameToParent() and SpatialObject.getDefaultAttachmentFrameForChildren()
        • the given frame is the default motion frame

      • getDefaultMotionFrame

        public ObjectFrame getDefaultMotionFrame()
        Gets the current defaultMotionFrame of the movable object. By default, the rootFrame of the object is the defaultMotionFrame (see SpatialObject.getRootFrame()).

        The defaultMotionFrame is used to perform motions commanded on the movable object (see IMovable).

        Changes of this property can be monitored by registering for the ObjectPropertyEvents on SpatialObject.getEventProvider(). This event is not fired on value equality changes.

        For further information about available events see TreeEvent and its subclasses.

        Specified by:
        getDefaultMotionFrame in interface IMovableObject
        Returns:
        the current defaultMotionFrame

      • move

        public IMotionContainer move(IMotion motion)
        Description copied from interface: IMovable
        Moves this object according to the given motion.

        The motion will be performed by a robot (or some other device) that should be found in the kinematic chain between this frame and the world origin (or the destination of the specified motion). If such a robot is not found - IllegalStateException will be thrown.
        If the specified motion is a cartesian motion - it is this frame that will reach the destination and/or follow the path defined by the motion. If the motion is joint specific - the motion directly affects the joints of the robot connected with this frame.

        Specified by:
        move in interface IMovable
        Parameters:
        motion - the motion that should be executed
        Returns:
        the execution container containing runtime information for the execution of the motion
